The World Health Organisation Director-General, Tedros Ghebreyesus, has congratulated Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala on her new appointment as World Trade Organisation, WTO, Director-General. DAILY POST reports that Okonjo-Iweala, Nigeria’s former Minister of Finance made history on Monday following her election as the first female DG of WTO. President Muhammadu Buhari and other Nigerians have congratulated her for the historic feat. Ghebreyesus, on his part in a congratulatory post to Okonjo-Iweala via his Twitter account on Monday, said the health agency looks forward to working with her. According to him, her great experience, skills and advocacy to tackle today’s challenges, makes her WTO’s perfect chief. “Glad to see my sister @NOIweala appointed @wto DirectorGeneral. “Your great experience, skills & advocacy to tackle today’s challenges, make you WTO’s perfect chief. “I look forward to working with you to help the world recover from,” he said.